</CO>
<LP>
   SOUTH SAN FRANCISCO, Calif. -- Guy F. Atkinson Co. said a
unit received a contract valued at about $35 million Canadian
(US$30.2 million) to modernize a paper mill in British
Columbia, Canada.
   The company said the unit, Commonwealth Construction Co.,
will install a new paper machine, winders, grinders and other
equipment for the Howe Sound Pulp &amp; Paper Co. mill. The
project is scheduled for completion in January.
</LP>
