<HL>
   Greyhound Restores
   Service to 286 Sites
</HL>
<DATE>
04/12/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4
</SO>
<CO>
   LABOR
</CO>
<IN>
MASS TRANSIT, BUS LINES, SUBWAYS, HIGHWAYS (TRA)
</IN>
<LP>
   DALLAS -- Greyhound Lines Inc. said it is restoring
service to 286 communities in a move the strike-bound bus
company said would increase its passenger service network by
28%.
   The company has been operating with replacement drivers
and union crossovers since March 2, when 9,400 members of the
Amalgamated Transit Union walked off the job in a contract
dispute over wages and workplace issues.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The unit of GLI Holding Co. said the increase, announced
just before the busy Easter travel weekend, boosts its daily
scheduled service to about 72% of pre-strike levels.
</TEXT>
