   DALLAS -- American Medical International Inc. said that it
signed a preliminary agreement valued at more than $100
million over five years calling for Perot Systems Corp. to
handle its data-processing and telecommunications operations.
   American Medical said the agreement is expected to reduce
its operating costs by at least $20 million a year, while
giving it and its hospitals access to newer hospital
data-processing products.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   American Medical owns acute-care and psychiatric
hospitals. Perot Systems, founded by Dallas computer magnate
H. Ross Perot, is a contractor of information systems.
