<HL>
   Raytheon Reports
   Net Increased 8.4%
   For the First Quarter
</HL>
<DATE>
04/12/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C17
</SO>
<CO>
   RTN
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
AEROSPACE (ARO)
</IN>
<LP>
   LEXINGTON, Mass. -- Raytheon Co. reported an 8.4% increase
in net income for the first quarter on a 7.3% revenue gain.
   The electronics, aircraft and missile manufacturer said
net income was $130.9 million, or $2 a share, compared with
$120.8 million, or $1.83 a share, for the 1989 first quarter.
Revenue rose to $2.23 billion from $2.07 billion.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In a statement, Raytheon said its total order backlog grew
to $9.49 billion, including funded U.S. government orders of
$6.84 billion. Backlog at the close of last year's first
quarter was $8.88 billion, including a government-funded
backlog of $6.78 billion.
   Thomas L. Phillips, chairman and chief executive, said
that in the first quarter, the electronics segment,
Raytheon's largest, performed well, while the aircraft and
energy-services segments continued rapid profit growth and
all five business units remained profitable. "Raytheon
continues to grow on the strength of its diversified
government and commercial business base," Mr. Phillips said.
   The company also said that its Beech Aircraft unit enjoyed
higher sales and improved profit margins. During the quarter,
Raytheon's dividend was raised to 60 cents a share from 55
cents.
</TEXT>
