<LP>
   Societe Generale reported in Paris that its consolidated
net profit rose 17% in 1989 and unveiled plans to increase
its net annual dividend to 15 francs (2.7 cents) a share from
13 francs (2.3 cents).
   Marc Vienot, chairman of the private-sector banking group,
told a news conference that the 1989 performance was "more
than acceptable," with consolidated net profit after payments
to minority interests climbing to 3.56 billion francs from
