operations was offset, however, by an "exceptional" rise in
profits from its asset management activity. He also noted
that Societe Generale's traditional commercial bank
operations continued to grow satisfactorily, with total loans
to customers rising 15% to 475 billion francs while client
deposits climbed 10% to 362 billion.
