<HL>
   Dividend Brief -- Woolworth Corp.:
   Retailer Sets 2-for-1 Split
   And Boosts Dividend 11%
</HL>
<DATE>
04/12/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C9
</SO>
<CO>
   Z
</CO>
<IN>
DIVIDENDS (DIV)
</IN>
<LP>
   Woolworth Corp. declared a 2-for-1 stock split, payable
May 31 to stock of record May 3 and increased its quarterly
dividend by 11%.
   The New York-based retailing concern raised its dividend
to 52 cents a share from 47 cents a share, on a pre-split
basis, payable June 1 to shares of record May 3.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   After the split, Woolworth said it will have 129 million
common shares outstanding and 158,000 shares of $2.20 Series
A convertible preferred. Each share of preferred will be
convertible into 5.68 shares of common, as compared with 2.84
shares before the split.
   The company said the actions reflect its "increasingly
strong financial performance." For the year ended Jan. 27,
the company earned $329 million, or $5.11 a share, on revenue
of $8.8 billion.
